mst [-e | -c] [--existance | --compare] [Resource-propertyname] [><=<>] [value-of-the-property]

** If you are trying to compare a resource property whose value is a time (i.e- modificationTime, currentTime etc.), 
the compared value-of-the-property must also be in a valid time format(yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss[.f])    

example:

mds -c modificationTime > 2014-01-01 

-- This will find all the files or directories which have been modified after the 1st Jan of 2014.

-- Resource property name can be any XPath expression  